http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Road-Safety-Week%E2%80%99-begins/article13998593.ece

“Road Safety Week”, a programme to create public awareness about the importance of traffic rules, began in the began on Wednesday, when an awareness rally was taken out and essay writing competition held for high school students.Mandya Superintendent of Police C.H. Sudheer Kumar Reddy flagged off the rally near his office. He appealed to road-users to adhere to traffic rules to make an accident-free district.Drivers and vehicle riders should wear seatbelts and helmets, he suggested. Police officials were present.Meanwhile, the Regional Transport Office had organised an essay writing competition on road safety, in which around 300 students participated. Motor vehicle inspector Sadrulla Sheriff and others were present.